        context_item("Warm-up — Activity Synthesis", "• “Which diagram best matches the equation in C?\nExplain.” (D because the equation shows that an\naddend is unknown and that it is not 27. It matches D\n\nbecause it shows that 27 plus the unknown is 40.)\n\n• “Why do all 4 go together?” (They all are related to\n\n. They all represent a relationship\n\nbetween 27, 13, and 40.)", line(109)),
        context_item("Activity 1 — Activity Synthesis", "• Invite 2–3 previously selected students to share how\nthey decided which cards go together.\n\n• Consider asking:\n\n◦ “How does the equation match the story\nproblem?”\n\n◦ “Is there another equation that could match the\nstory problem? Explain why or why not.”", line(219)),
        context_item("Lesson Synthesis", "Display student work samples for the story about Noah’s and Kiran’s seeds that show an accurate diagram, an addition\nequation that represents the story, and a subtraction equation that represents the story.\n\n“Do both equations match the story and the diagram? Explain.” (Yes. Each equation shows the total amount of seeds\nand Noah’s seeds. The question mark shows Kiran’s seeds. You could show how Noah’s seeds and Kiran’s seeds are\nrelated with addition or subtraction.)\n\n“Which helps you make sense of a story—a diagram, an equation, or both?”", line(424))
