    [
        context_item("Warm-up — Activity Synthesis", "• “How did you choose which numbers to add first?” (I\n\nlooked for ways to make a ten. I looked for ways to\n\nuse sums I’ve done before. I added tens first then I\ntried to make tens with the ones.)", line(111)),
        context_item("Activity 1 — Activity Synthesis", "• Invite previously identified students to share their\ntape diagram and equation for each part.\n• “How did _____ represent the problem? How does\neach representation show the story problem?”\n\n• Display\n\n• “How does this equation represent Andre’s seeds?” (It\nshows all the seeds he has in one equation.)\n• “What are other ways we could add to find the sum?”\n\n(We could add 25 and 35 first. Then add 17. We could\nadd 17 and 35 and then add 25.)", line(188)),
        context_item("Activity 2 — Activity Synthesis", "• Invite previously selected students to share how they\nrepresented and solved the story problem.\n• Consider asking:\n◦ “How are these ways of representing the story\nthe same?”\n◦ “How are they different?”\n• “How does each way match what happened in the\nstory?” (The numbers match the seeds in the story.\nThey all show adding or putting the seeds together.\nThat matches what happened in the story because\nPriya kept getting more seeds.)\n• “How is this story different from the other stories we\nhave solved?” (There weren’t just two numbers to\nadd or subtract. There wasn’t just one thing that\nhappened.)", line(314)),
        context_item("Lesson Synthesis", "“In this lesson, we practiced making sense of and solving different kinds of story problems and using what we know\nabout adding and subtracting two-digit numbers.”\n\n“What do you do to make sense of and solve story problems?”\n\n“What ideas for solving story problems have you learned from others?", line(334))
