        context_item("Activity 1 — Activity Synthesis", "• Invite 3–5 previously selected students to share their\nrectangles and how they created them.\n• “This is called the 'multiplication table.' The numbers\nalong the top and on the left side are the 'factors,' or\nthe numbers we are multiplying.”\n• “The number in the lower right square of the\nrectangle is the value of the product. The value of the\nproduct lines up with a factor above it and a factor to\nthe left of it.”\n• “We could represent the factors and the product in\nthe last table in the first group of tables with 3 times\n4 equals 12.”\n• Display\n• “How is the multiplication table different from other\nways we’ve represented multiplication?” (It’s harder\nto see the factors. There’s no equal sign. We can\npicture a rectangle that helps us find the product.)", line(205)),
        context_item("Activity 2 — Activity Synthesis", "• “What patterns did you find in the products of 5?\nHow did you show them with equations?”\n• “Why is that pattern happening?”\n\n• “What other patterns do we see in the table? How\ncould we show the patterns with equations? Why are\nthese patterns happening?”", line(287)),
