        context_item("Lesson Synthesis", "“Today we found the nearest multiple of 100 and the nearest multiple of 10 to a given number. When we name another\nnumber that is close to a given number, we are rounding the given number. For example, we can round 568 to 570 or\nto 600. Often, the numbers we use for rounding are multiples of 10 or multiples of 100.”\n\n“If we want to use the word round to say ‘find the nearest multiple of 10,’ we can say ‘round to the nearest ten.’ We can\nuse the word round with hundreds, too. Instead of saying ‘find the nearest multiple of 100,’ we can say, ‘round to the\nnearest hundred.’”", line(355))
