        context_item("Activity 2 — Student Task Statement", "The table shows the numbers of people in different\nparts of a school at noon during a school day.\nAndre and Lin are trying to estimate the number of\npeople in the whole school. Andre plans to round\nthe numbers to the nearest hundred. Lin plans to\nround them to the nearest ten.\n\n1. Make a prediction: Whose estimate will be\n\ngreater? Explain your reasoning.\n\n2. Work with a partner to find Andre's and Lin’s\n\nestimates. Record them in the table. Then find\nthe totals.\n\nAndre's       Lin's\nestimate     estimate\n\nlocation     number\n(nearest     (nearest\nhundred)       ten)\nplayground       94\ncafeteria      163\nart room        36\nlibrary        49\n\nclassrooms      216\ngymnasium       109\n\nmusic\nroom\n\ntotal\n\n3. Make 2 observations about the completed\n\ntable. Was your prediction correct?", line(251)),
