        context_item("Activity 2 — Student Task Statement", "For each problem:\n\na. Write an equation with a symbol for the\nunknown quantity to represent the situation.\n\nb. Solve the problem and find the unknown\nnumber in the equation. Be prepared to explain\n\nyour reasoning.\n\n1. Kiran had 32 paper clips. He gave each student\n4 paper clips. How many students received\npaper clips?\na. Equation: _______________________\nb. Solution: _______________________\n\n2. There are 28 books in 4 stacks. Each stack has\nthe same number of books. How many books\nare in each stack?\na. Equation: _______________________\n\nb. Solution: _______________________\n\n3. There are 6 boxes. Each box has 8 erasers.\nHow many erasers are there?\na. Equation: _______________________\n\nb. Solution: _______________________\n\n4. Lin has 36 sticky notes. She places 6 sticky\n\nnotes on each notebook. How many notebooks\nhave sticky notes?\n\na. Equation: _______________________\n\nb. Solution: _______________________", line(255)),
