    [
        context_item("Activity 1 — Activity Synthesis", "• “Find another person in the room who you did not\nwork with and describe the rules of your game and\nhow someone wins.”\n• Instruct these partners to ask each other this\nquestion: “How did your group redesign the game?”\n(We made each ball worth a different number of\npoints. We recorded when the game started and\nended.)", line(258)),
        context_item("Lesson Synthesis", "Invite previously identified groups to describe the rules of their original and then their redesigned game.\n\n“What changes do you notice?” (In the redesigned game, you have to multiply to find your total number of points. In the\nredesigned game, players are timed, and get more points if you finish faster.)\n\n“What questions do you have for the designers of the game?” (How did you decide on how many points each ball was\nworth? How did you decide how far someone should stand from the cups?)\n\n“What decisions did you make today as you designed and redesigned your game?” (We had to decide what would make\nthe game fair. We had to decide on rules for the game that made it challenging, but not too hard. When we redesigned\nthe game, we had to decide which things from the list would work best with our game.)\n\nConsider having students respond to the previous question as a journal prompt.", line(271))
    ],
    source('knowledge/geometry/corpus/im_teacher_guides/grade3/unit6/lesson16.md')).

