        context_item("Lesson Synthesis", "“Today we used base-ten blocks, grids, and drawings to represent multi-digit numbers. We also used groups of\nhundreds to build 10,000.”\n\n“In first grade, we learned that 10 ones are in each unit of ten. In second grade, we learned that 10 tens are in each unit\nof one hundred. If we count 10 units of a hundred, we have a thousand, which is a new unit.”\n\n“Where in this class chart do you see ten of something making a new unit?” (Ten of the hundred grids make a row or a\nunit of one thousand. Ten of the thousand rows make a unit of ten-thousand.)\n\n“How might we represent a number like 13,000?” (Add three more rows of 1,000 to the chart.)\n\n“What do you think the next unit will be after ten-thousands?” (hundred-thousands or millions)\n\n“Ten groups of ten-thousand makes a new unit, hundred-thousand. We will learn about this unit in future lessons.”", line(314))
