        context_item("Activity 1 — Activity Synthesis", "• Invite selected students to share their conclusions\nabout the relationship between pounds and ounces.\n• Highlight explanations that make it clear that 1\npound is 16 times as much or as heavy as 1 ounce.\n• Display the table and invite students to share the\namounts in ounces and their reasoning.\n• If needed, point out that the abbreviation “lb” is used\nfor pounds and “oz” is used for ounces.", line(210)),
        context_item("Lesson Synthesis", "“Today we learned about the relationship between pounds and ounces and solved some problems that involve those\nmeasurements.”\n\n“When you weigh yourself, the scale likely gives your weight in pounds. If the scale is set to measure in ounces, will the\nnumber be greater or less? How much greater or less? Why is that?” (Greater, 16 times greater because there are 16\nounces in 1 pound, so the amount in pounds needs to be multiplied by 16 to get the equivalent in ounces.)\n\n“How is the relationship between pounds and ounces like that between kilograms and grams?” (One unit is larger than\nthe other.)\n\n“How is it different from the relationship between kilograms and grams?” (In pounds and ounces, the larger unit is 16\ntimes the smaller unit. In kilograms and grams, the larger unit is 1,000 times the smaller unit.)", line(312))
