    [
        context_item("Warm-up — Activity Synthesis", "• “The numbers tell us how far each animal can jump.”\n• Ask students to decide if each of the following\nstatements is true or false and to share their\nresponses and their reasoning:\n\n◦ “A rabbit can jump 10 times as far as a\n\ndolphin.” (That's false because a dolphin can\njump nearly 10 times as far as a rabbit.)\n◦ “A dolphin can jump as far as a frog.” (That's false\nbecause a dolphin can jump farther than a frog.)\n• “What other comparison statements can you make\nabout how far these animals can jump?” (A dolphin\ncan jump 10 times as far as a rabbit. A frog can jump\nalmost 4 times as far as a rabbit.)\n• “We are going to keep thinking about making\n\ncomparisons in our first activity today.”", line(110)),
        context_item("Activity 1 — Activity Synthesis", "• Have students post their cards for all to see for the\n\nGallery Walk in the next activity.", line(199)),
        context_item("Activity 2 — Activity Synthesis", "• Invite students to share false statements they found\n\nand their reasoning about how they knew the\n\nstatement was false.\n\n• Invite students to share their revised statements and\nthe revisions they made.", line(270)),
        context_item("Lesson Synthesis", "“Today, we wrote some comparison statements and figured out if other groups' statements were true or false.”\n\n“How did you decide what information to use as you wrote your comparison statements?” (I like dragonflies, so I\ncompared their speed to the speeds of other animals. I looked for measurements that could be compared with\nmultiplication, like how the bottlenose dolphin can live about twice as long as the southern elephant seal.)\n\nConsider having students respond to the previous question as a journal prompt.", line(287))
