    [
        context_item("Warm-up — Activity Synthesis", "• “How many spoons should Jada get to put on the\ntable?” (She should get 6 spoons. There should be\nthe same number of bowls and spoons.)\n• “What information helped you figure out how many\nspoons Jada should get? How did it help you?” (It\nhelped to know how many bowls there were. Each\nperson needs a spoon to use with a bowl.)", line(113)),
        context_item("Activity 1 — Activity Synthesis", "• “Some people shared that Tyler needs to know what\nfood is being served for dinner. Does Tyler need to\nknow what food is being served for dinner? What\nmakes you think that?” (Yes, because then he will\nknow if everyone needs a fork or a spoon. No,\nbecause we always give everyone a fork and a knife.)", line(183)),
        context_item("Activity 2 — Activity Synthesis", "• “What parts of your partner’s display helped you\nlearn what they would need to set the table?” (It\nhelped when they wrote numbers to show how many\nthey needed. I liked when they drew a picture to\nshow the plates and cups.)\n• “What kind of food did you think about when you\nmade your display? What if a different kind of food\nwas served for dinner instead? Would you need to do\nanything differently?” (Yes, because if we were having\nsoup, I would give everyone bowls and spoons\ninstead of plates and forks. No, because we always\nuse forks and spoons at dinner.)", line(255)),
        context_item("Lesson Synthesis", "“Today we thought about sharing meals with our families and what we need to do to set the table for meals.”\n\n“What were some things that you needed to know, or guess, to set the table? What are some things that you did not\nneed to know?” (We needed to know how many people there would be. We did not need to know what color the napkins\nwere or if we would drink apple juice or orange juice.)\n\nKindergarten                                    CC BY NC 2024", line(272))
